Larry McVoy writes:
> The proposal is this:
> 
>     a) get VA or Penguin to sponsor the hardware and the test lab,
>        I'll talk to them and try and make that happen.
>     b) create a test lab with enough clients to generate the load
>        with a setup like so:
> 
> 		    [ server ]
> 		        |
> 		       gbit
> 			|
> 		    [ router ]
> 		    /  / \  \
> 		   /  /   \  \
> 		  /  /     \  \
> 		 c  c  ...  c  c
> 
I'd also suggest that the server be set up with multiple 100 Mb cards
(aka the Netcraft test).
>     d) put all of this behind a benchmark.valinux.com firewall and give
>        developers ssh access into the playpen.
Yep.
> Any interest in this?  Seems like it would be a cool setup for this
> and for http test loads.  And once we get it going, it might be a
> nice setup to challenge microsloth with...
I think it's a very good idea, and I'm kind of surprised that it
hasn't happened before this. I think it's time that we pooled our
resources so that we can routinely do these kinds of tests.
				Regards,
					Richard....
